OL,3,COvercrowded and understaffed -
OL,4,CScottish prisons pushed to "crisis
OL,5,Cpoint"
OL,7,FPhil Fairlie, Assistant General
OL,8,FSecretary of the Prison Officers
OL,9,FAssociation for Scotland, said:
OL,10,F"Overcrowding makes everything more
OL,11,Fdifficult.
OL,13,F"We do not have enough staff to manage
OL,14,Fa population of this size. We need an
OL,15,Finvestment in staff numbers."
OL,17,FSince early 2024 hundreds of prisoners
OL,18,Fhave been released early in Scotland,
OL,19,Fin a bid to alleviate the pressure.
